The paper discusses big data processing engines, which are commonly used in distributed computing and data management. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions benchmarks and performance evaluation, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The Kappa architecture mentioned in the abstract is related to stream processing, which is a subfield of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of cloud computing is also mentioned, which could fall under cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
